{
  "texts": [
    "A malicious client can warn NDN routers about invalid material that behaves as valid in the proposed scheme.",
    "Ullah et al. (2020) suggest an On Demand lightweight identity-based signature technique to mitigate a CPA in an NDN based on IoT, as can be seen in Fig. 16.",
    "According to the authors, in order to register themselves with the trusted network management and provide their identities in the manner outlined in step 1, both the consumer and the provider of the material are required to comply.",
    "In the second stage, the network manager uses the members' identities to generate private keys, which are then distributed to each of the participants (client and provider).",
    "In this scheme, when a client show interest in content (A), which is shown in step 3, the provider on receiving the request signs the content (A) with the private key and forwards it to the client as seen in step 4."
  ]
}